 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT PROPOSAL: Module Decomposition of >150 KB Files — Priority 5 (Sessions 50-52). PROBLEM: Six kernel files exceed 150 KB: guidance.rs (260 KB, 7119 lines), store.rs (227 KB, 5848 lines), seed.rs (210 KB, 5314 lines), concept.rs (202 KB, 5362 lines), schema.rs (184 KB, 4957 lines), bilateral.rs (173 KB, 4769 lines). This violates NEG-008 (no monolithic files). guidance.rs contains at least 4 distinct concerns: session management, methodology scoring, context assembly, routing integration, footer injection. When an AI agent works on guidance, it must load 260 KB of context to touch any part. SOLUTION: Convert each of the 6 files from single files to module directories. Example for guidance.rs: guidance/mod.rs (re-exports), guidance/session.rs (session management), guidance/scoring.rs (methodology scoring), guidance/context.rs (context assembly), guidance/footer.rs (injection). No behavioral changes — pure structural refactor. Can be parallelized across 6 agents (one per file) with disjoint file sets. FIRST-PRINCIPLES JUSTIFICATION: This directly improves the system's ability to learn about itself (meta-convergence). Smaller files mean: (1) more precise bilateral scans (spec↔impl links are per-file), (2) better coverage attribution (F(S) C component more granular), (3) cleaner spec↔impl links (each module maps to a spec namespace), (4) reduced context load for AI agents (30 KB vs 260 KB). The system that helps organizations learn should be structurally organized for its own learning. VERIFICATION APPROACH: (1) cargo test passes before and after (zero behavioral change). (2) No new warnings from cargo clippy. (3) File count increases, max file size decreases below 100 KB. (4) All existing spec↔impl links remain valid. DEPENDENCIES: Should follow the verification sprint (Priority 2) to avoid moving targets. No code dependencies — pure refactor. UNBLOCKS: AI agent effectiveness on kernel modifications, structure discovery loop (OBSERVER-5), future refactoring velocity. TRACES TO: NEG-008, OBSERVER-5 (structure discovery), C5 (traceability)."
